  "instructions": [
    "Dice kabocha into 1-inch cubes.",
    "Rinse and drain chickpeas.",
    "Warm coconut milk with spices for 2 minutes to release flavors.",
    "Pour mixture into a mason jar along with diced kabocha, chickpeas, tomato puree, and vegetable broth.",
    "Stir gently until all ingredients are evenly coated.",
    "Seal the jar and place it in a pot of simmering water, ensuring water level reaches halfway up the jar.",
    "Cook on low heat for 45 minutes, stirring halfway through to prevent sticking.",
    "After cooking, remove jar, stir, add lemon juice, and garnish with cilantro before serving."
